  16. (* Pretty-printing of pseudo machine code *)

  18. open Format
  19. open Cmm
  20. open Reg
  21. open Mach
  22. open Interval

  24. ‌let reg ppf r =
  25.   if not (Reg.anonymous r) then
  26.     fprintf ppf "%s" (Reg.name r)
  27.   else
  28.     fprintf ppf "%s"
  29.       (match r.typ with Val -> "V" | Addr -> "A" | Int -> "I" | Float -> "F");
  30.   fprintf ppf "/%i" r.stamp;
  31.   begin match r.loc with
  32.   | Unknown -> ()
  33.   | Reg r ->
  34.       fprintf ppf "[%s]" (Proc.register_name r)
  35.   | Stack(Local s) ->
  36.       fprintf ppf "[s%i]" s
  37.   | Stack(Incoming s) ->
  38.       fprintf ppf "[si%i]" s
  39.   | Stack(Outgoing s) ->
  40.       fprintf ppf "[so%i]" s
  41.   | Stack(Domainstate s) ->
  42.       fprintf ppf "[ds%i]" s
  43.   end

  45. ‌let regs ppf v =
  46.   match Array.length v with
  47.   | 0 -> ()
  48.   | 1 -> reg ppf v.(0)
  49.   | n -> reg ppf v.(0);
  50.          for i = 1 to n-1 do fprintf ppf " %a" reg v.(i) done

  52. ‌let regset ppf s =
  53.   let first = ref true in
  54.   Reg.Set.iter
  55.     (fun r ->
  56.       if !first then begin first := false; fprintf ppf "%a" reg r end
  57.       else fprintf ppf "@ %a" reg r)
  58.     s

  60. ‌let regsetaddr ppf s =
  61.   let first = ref true in
  62.   Reg.Set.iter
  63.     (fun r ->
  64.       if !first then begin first := false; fprintf ppf "%a" reg r end
  65.       else fprintf ppf "@ %a" reg r;
  66.       match r.typ with
  67.       | Val -> fprintf ppf "*"
  68.       | Addr -> fprintf ppf "!"
  69.       | _ -> ())
  70.     s

  72. let intcomp = function
  73.   | Isigned c -> Printf.sprintf " %ss " (Printcmm.integer_comparison c)
  74.   | Iunsigned c -> Printf.sprintf " %su " (Printcmm.integer_comparison c)

  76. ‌let floatcomp c =
  77.     Printf.sprintf " %sf " (Printcmm.float_comparison c)

  79. ‌let intop = function
  80.   | Iadd -> " + "
  81.   | Isub -> " - "
  82.   | Imul -> " * "
  83.   | Imulh -> " *h "
  84.   | Idiv -> " div "
  85.   | Imod -> " mod "
  86.   | Iand -> " & "
  87.   | Ior ->  " | "
  88.   | Ixor -> " ^ "
  89.   | Ilsl -> " << "
  90.   | Ilsr -> " >>u "
  91.   | Iasr -> " >>s "
  92.   | Icomp cmp -> intcomp cmp
  93.   | Icheckbound -> Printf.sprintf "check > "

  95. ‌let test tst ppf arg =
  96.   match tst with
  97.   | Itruetest -> reg ppf arg.(0)
  98.   | Ifalsetest -> fprintf ppf "not %a" reg arg.(0)
  99.   | Iinttest cmp -> fprintf ppf "%a%s%a" reg arg.(0) (intcomp cmp) reg arg.(1)
  100.   | Iinttest_imm(cmp, n) -> fprintf ppf "%a%s%i" reg arg.(0) (intcomp cmp) n
  101.   | Ifloattest cmp ->
  102.       fprintf ppf "%a%s%a"
  103.        reg arg.(0) (floatcomp cmp) reg arg.(1)
  104.   | Ieventest -> fprintf ppf "%a & 1 == 0" reg arg.(0)
  105.   | Ioddtest -> fprintf ppf "%a & 1 == 1" reg arg.(0)

  107. ‌let operation op arg ppf res =
  108.   if Array.length res > 0 then fprintf ppf "%a := " regs res;
  109.   match op with
  110.   | Imove -> regs ppf arg
  111.   | Ispill -> fprintf ppf "%a (spill)" regs arg
  112.   | Ireload -> fprintf ppf "%a (reload)" regs arg
  113.   | Iconst_int n -> fprintf ppf "%s" (Nativeint.to_string n)
  114.   | Iconst_float f -> fprintf ppf "%F" (Int64.float_of_bits f)
  115.   | Iconst_symbol s -> fprintf ppf "\"%s\"" s
  116.   | Icall_ind -> fprintf ppf "call %a" regs arg
  117.   | Icall_imm { func; } -> fprintf ppf "call \"%s\" %a" func regs arg
  118.   | Itailcall_ind -> fprintf ppf "tailcall %a" regs arg
  119.   | Itailcall_imm { func; } -> fprintf ppf "tailcall \"%s\" %a" func regs arg
  120.   | Iextcall { func; alloc; _ } ->
  121.       fprintf ppf "extcall \"%s\" %a%s" func regs arg
  122.       (if alloc then "" else " (noalloc)")
  123.   | Istackoffset n ->
  124.       fprintf ppf "offset stack %i" n
  125.   | Iload { memory_chunk; addressing_mode; mutability=Immutable; is_atomic } ->
  126.       fprintf ppf "%s %a[%a]"
  127.        (Printcmm.chunk memory_chunk)
  128.        (fun pp a -> if a then fprintf pp "atomic" else ()) is_atomic
  129.        (Arch.print_addressing reg addressing_mode) arg
  130.   | Iload { memory_chunk; addressing_mode; mutability=Mutable; is_atomic } ->
  131.       fprintf ppf "%s %a mut[%a]"
  132.        (Printcmm.chunk memory_chunk)
  133.        (fun pp a -> if a then fprintf pp "atomic" else ()) is_atomic
  134.        (Arch.print_addressing reg addressing_mode) arg
  135.   | Istore(chunk, addr, is_assign) ->
  136.       fprintf ppf "%s[%a] := %a %s"
  137.        (Printcmm.chunk chunk)
  138.        (Arch.print_addressing reg addr)
  139.        (Array.sub arg 1 (Array.length arg - 1))
  140.        reg arg.(0)
  141.        (if is_assign then "(assign)" else "(init)")
  142.   | Ialloc { bytes = n; } ->
  143.     fprintf ppf "alloc %i" n;
  144.   | Iintop(op) -> fprintf ppf "%a%s%a" reg arg.(0) (intop op) reg arg.(1)
  145.   | Iintop_imm(op, n) -> fprintf ppf "%a%s%i" reg arg.(0) (intop op) n
  146.   | Icompf cmp -> fprintf ppf "%a%s%a" reg arg.(0) (floatcomp cmp) reg arg.(1)
  147.   | Inegf -> fprintf ppf "-f %a" reg arg.(0)
  148.   | Iabsf -> fprintf ppf "absf %a" reg arg.(0)
  149.   | Iaddf -> fprintf ppf "%a +f %a" reg arg.(0) reg arg.(1)
  150.   | Isubf -> fprintf ppf "%a -f %a" reg arg.(0) reg arg.(1)
  151.   | Imulf -> fprintf ppf "%a *f %a" reg arg.(0) reg arg.(1)
  152.   | Idivf -> fprintf ppf "%a /f %a" reg arg.(0) reg arg.(1)
  153.   | Ifloatofint -> fprintf ppf "floatofint %a" reg arg.(0)
  154.   | Iintoffloat -> fprintf ppf "intoffloat %a" reg arg.(0)
  155.   | Iopaque -> fprintf ppf "opaque %a" reg arg.(0)
  156.   | Ispecific op ->
  157.       Arch.print_specific_operation reg op ppf arg
  158.   | Idls_get -> fprintf ppf "dls_get"
  159.   | Ipoll { return_label } ->
  160.       fprintf ppf "poll call";
  161.       match return_label with
  162.       | None -> ()
  163.       | Some return_label ->
  164.         fprintf ppf " returning to L%d" return_label

  166. let rec instr ppf i =
  167.   if !Clflags.dump_live then begin
  168.     fprintf ppf "@[<1>{%a" regsetaddr i.live;
  169.     if Array.length i.arg > 0 then fprintf ppf "@ +@ %a" regs i.arg;
  170.     fprintf ppf "}@]@,";
  171.   end;
  172.   begin match i.desc with
  173.   | Iend -> ()
  174.   | Iop op ->
  175.       operation op i.arg ppf i.res
  176.   | Ireturn ->
  177.       fprintf ppf "return %a" regs i.arg
  178.   | Iifthenelse(tst, ifso, ifnot) ->
  179.       fprintf ppf "@[<v 2>if %a then@,%a" (test tst) i.arg instr ifso;
  180.       begin match ifnot.desc with
  181.       | Iend -> ()
  182.       | _ -> fprintf ppf "@;<0 -2>else@,%a" instr ifnot
  183.       end;
  184.       fprintf ppf "@;<0 -2>endif@]"
  185.   | Iswitch(index, cases) ->
  186.       fprintf ppf "switch %a" reg i.arg.(0);
  187.       for i = 0 to Array.length cases - 1 do
  188.         fprintf ppf "@,@[<v 2>@[";
  189.         for j = 0 to Array.length index - 1 do
  190.           if index.(j) = i then fprintf ppf "case %i:@," j
  191.         done;
  192.         fprintf ppf "@]@,%a@]" instr cases.(i)
  193.       done;
  194.       fprintf ppf "@,endswitch"
  195.   | Icatch(flag, handlers, body) ->
  196.       fprintf ppf "@[<v 2>catch%a@,%a@;<0 -2>with"
  197.         Printcmm.rec_flag flag instr body;
  198. ‌      let h (nfail, handler) =
  199.         fprintf ppf "(%d)@,%a@;" nfail instr handler in
  200. ‌      let rec aux = function
  201.         | [] -> ()
  202.         | [v] -> h v
  203.         | v :: t ->
  204.             h v;
  205.             fprintf ppf "@ and";
  206.             aux t
  207.       in
  208.       aux handlers;
  209.       fprintf ppf "@;<0 -2>endcatch@]"
  210.   | Iexit i ->
  211.       fprintf ppf "exit(%d)" i
  212.   | Itrywith(body, handler) ->
  213.       fprintf ppf "@[<v 2>try@,%a@;<0 -2>with@,%a@;<0 -2>endtry@]"
  214.              instr body instr handler
  215.   | Iraise k ->
  216.       fprintf ppf "%s %a" (Lambda.raise_kind k) reg i.arg.(0)
  217.   end;
  218.   if not (Debuginfo.is_none i.dbg) && !Clflags.locations then
  219.     fprintf ppf "%s" (Debuginfo.to_string i.dbg);
  220.   begin match i.next.desc with
  221.     Iend -> ()
  222.   | _ -> fprintf ppf "@,%a" instr i.next
  223.   end

  225. ‌let fundecl ppf f =
  226.   let dbg =
  227.     if Debuginfo.is_none f.fun_dbg || not !Clflags.locations then
  228.       ""
  229.     else
  230.       " " ^ Debuginfo.to_string f.fun_dbg in
  231.   fprintf ppf "@[<v 2>%s(%a)%s@,%a@]"
  232.     f.fun_name regs f.fun_args dbg instr f.fun_body

  234. ‌let phase msg ppf f =
  235.   fprintf ppf "*** %s@.%a@." msg fundecl f

  237. ‌let interference ppf r =
  238.   let interf ppf =
  239.    List.iter
  240.     (fun r -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" reg r)
  241.     r.interf in
  242.   fprintf ppf "@[<2>%a:%t@]@." reg r interf

  244. ‌let interferences ppf () =
  245.   fprintf ppf "*** Interferences@.";
  246.   List.iter (interference ppf) (Reg.all_registers())

  248. ‌let interval ppf i =
  249.   let interv ppf =
  250.     List.iter
  251.       (fun r -> fprintf ppf "@ [%d;%d]" r.rbegin r.rend)
  252.       i.ranges in
  253.   fprintf ppf "@[<2>%a:%t@]@." reg i.reg interv

  255. ‌let intervals ppf (intervals : Interval.result) =
  256.   fprintf ppf "*** Intervals@.";
  257.   List.iter (interval ppf) intervals.fixed_intervals;
  258.   List.iter (interval ppf) intervals.intervals

  260. ‌let preference ppf r =
  261.   let prefs ppf =
  262.     List.iter
  263.       (fun (r, w) -> fprintf ppf "@ %a weight %i" reg r w)
  264.       r.prefer in
  265.   fprintf ppf "@[<2>%a: %t@]@." reg r prefs

  267. ‌let preferences ppf () =
  268.   fprintf ppf "*** Preferences@.";
  269.   List.iter (preference ppf) (Reg.all_registers())
